		<description><![CDATA[<p>In this lesson I'm going to show you the real secret to learning the fingerboard... And... if you follow and learn the concepts in this lesson, you're going to be able to play ANY groove over ANY chord, ANYWHERE on...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/can-master-fingerboard-just-hand-full-shapes.html">How you can master the fingerboard &#8211; with just a hand full of shapes!</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In this lesson I'm going to show you the real secret to learning the <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/improvisation/how-to-unlock-your-bass-fingerboard-epic-scale-exercise.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">fingerboard</a>...</p>
<p>And... if you follow and learn the concepts in this lesson, you're going to be able to play ANY <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/groove-buster-ultimate-timing-exercise-bass-players.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">groove</a> over ANY <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/chords/playing-chords-on-bass-getting-your-voice-leading-together.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">chord</a>, ANYWHERE on the <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-tips/easily-memorise-notes-bass-fingerboard.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">fretboard</a>... without having to move your hand to a new position...</p>
<p>How?!</p>
<p>All the information you need will be accessible to you and <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/mastering-your-bass-fingerboard.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">directly under your fingers</a> - wherever you are on the fingerboard.</p>
<p>Oh, and just if you're wondering... it's NOTHING to do with <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/beginners/learn-notes-bass-guitar-l197.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">knowing your notes</a>.</p>
<p>As always, I'd love to hear from you guys in the comments section under the video... if you've had any big wins or difficulties when finding your way around the fingerboard - leave a comment and let us all know all about your journey!</p>
<p>Ready to jump in?! Let's do this...</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
<p>PS. If you enjoy this lesson you should seriously check out the <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/courses/harmonic-layering-a-real-world-approach-to-arpeggios-chord-tones-and-scales" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Harmonic layering course</a> in the course library here at SBL. It's the most in-depth video course ever created that solely focused on arpeggios, scales, modes - and exactly how as a bass player you can use them in a practical way. <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/courses/harmonic-layering-a-real-world-approach-to-arpeggios-chord-tones-and-scales" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Click here to check it out</a>. If you're already a member here at SBL you can login and jump into this course right now... if you're not a member yet, just <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">grab your 14 day FREE trial today</a> which will give you access to every course here at SBL (over 25 of them!) and WAY more!</p>
