<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/groove-buster" target="_blank">To Download The Backing Track For This Lesson Click Here</a></h2>
<p>
<p>===</p>
<p>It’s one thing to think you’ve got good time… but do you really?</p>
<p>Well, In the this lesson I’m going to put YOUR timing to the test!</p>
<p>And don’t worry… you’re going to hear me messing up too… we all need to work on our time ;)</p>
<p><strong>Important:</strong> I’ve put a link underneath the video so you can download the corresponding backing track you’ll need for this exercise.</p>
<p>As always… I love to hear back from you guys, so let me know how you get on with this exercise in the comments under the video!</p>
<p>See you in the shed…</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
<p>PS. If you enjoy this exercise and <em>really</em> want to get your time together (which you should do!)... check our <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/courses/a-masterclass-in-time-and-groove-development" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">time and groove development course</a> here at ScottsBassLessons. It's a detailed step by step curriculum of time and groove exercises specifically designed for bass players. Trust me... it'll make a <em>BIG</em> difference to your time feel and groove!</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/groove-buster-ultimate-timing-exercise-bass-players.html">&#8220;The Groove Buster&#8221;&#8230; the ultimate timing exercise for bass players</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
