		<title>Deeper Underground &#8211; Bass Line Analysis (L#220)</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/deeper-underground-bass-line-analysis-220.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/deeper-underground-bass-line-analysis-220.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 10 Nov 2016 12:36:35 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Travis Moore]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Bass Lines & Grooves]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=15353</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>=== In this lesson I'm going to teach you one of my all time favourite synth style bass lines - "Deeper Underground" by Jamiroquai. But there's more to it than just teaching you a great riff! One of the questions...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/deeper-underground-bass-line-analysis-220.html">Deeper Underground &#8211; Bass Line Analysis (L#220)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><div><a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-academy" class="post_cta">Full tab/notation & workbook available to Academy members &raquo;</a></div><div class="video_wrap "><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Nr0vvN2rZlg" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div></p>
<p>===</p>
<p>In this lesson I'm going to teach you one of my all time favourite synth style bass lines - "Deeper Underground" by Jamiroquai.</p>
<p>But there's more to it than just teaching you a <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/quick-riff/pino-palladino-quick-riff.html" target="_blank">great riff</a>!</p>
<p>One of the questions I get asked time and time again is "How do you do those cool little squiggles... when you slide really fast with one finger between two frets"...</p>
<p>Well the great thing about Deeper Underground is that, by learning the riff, you're going to learn exactly how to achieve these 'squiggles' (also commonly know as '<a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/sting-technique-add-grease-bass-fills-grooves-l191.html" target="_blank">stings</a>') as you have to learn how to use them to play the riff correctly.</p>
<p>There are a couple of cool tricks I'm going to show you in this lesson to achieve the right sound when you use this <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/killer-exercise-to-build-your-technique-205.html" target="_blank">technique</a>. They're pretty simple - but not that obvious when you first start trying to master it.</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed...</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/deeper-underground-bass-line-analysis-220.html">Deeper Underground &#8211; Bass Line Analysis (L#220)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
