		<title>Jazz Style Sweeping Lick for Bass &#8211; (L#211)</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/jazz-style-sweeping-lick-l210.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/jazz-style-sweeping-lick-l210.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 02 Sep 2016 10:32:25 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Travis Moore]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Bass Lines & Grooves]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=14802</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>Non Academy members can grab the PDF with Tab and Notation by clicking here. === A few weeks ago I uploaded a short video to the SBL Instagram channel where I was playing a fast jazz style sweeping lick (a...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/jazz-style-sweeping-lick-l210.html">Jazz Style Sweeping Lick for Bass &#8211; (L#211)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><div><a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-academy" class="post_cta">Full tab/notation & workbook available to Academy members &raquo;</a></div><div class="video_wrap "><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OtHR0tfIBeM" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div></p>
<p><a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/sweeping-lick-pdf">Non Academy members can grab the PDF with Tab and Notation by clicking here.</a></p>
<p>===</p>
<p>A few weeks ago I uploaded a short video to the <a href="https://www.instagram.com/scottsbasslessons/" target="_blank">SBL Instagram channel</a> where I was playing a fast <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/improvisation/walking-bass-substitutions-todd-johnson.html" target="_blank">jazz</a> style sweeping <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/quick-lick/modern-jazz-style-lick-quick-riff-201.html" target="_blank">lick</a> (a technique usually associated with Guitar).</p>
<p>A few days later I'd received nearly 30 direct messages on Instagram asking me, I quote... "What the heck was that sweeping lick you just played?!"...</p>
<p>So, I figured it'd be fun to break it down for you and show you exactly how I'm achieving that kind of sound and <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/the-ultimate-speed-exercise-for-bass-players.html" target="_blank">speed</a> (hint: it's a lot to do with <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/3-killer-hammer-on-development-exercises-for-bass-players.html" target="_blank">hammer ons</a>, pull off's and raking).</p>
<p>If you're into jazz style licks, playing 'out', and generally getting your shred on - this lesson is for you!</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed...</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
<p>PS. There's some REALLY exciting stuff coming up that you're going to want to keep a look out for...</p>
