<p>===</p>
<p>In this lesson I'm going to show you one of (if not 'the') most important chord sequences I have ever learned.</p>
<p>If you haven't noticed yet - most songs are built from the same types of chord movements... and learning these will be HUGE for your bass playing and overall musicianship.</p>
<p><strong>In this lesson you're going to learn:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>One of the most important chord sequences you'll ever learn</li>
<li>Why you should be focusing regularly on common chord movements - and what they are</li>
<li>Why we use numbers to explain chord sequences (and how it works)</li>
<li>Why recognition of common chord sequences will be AMAZING for your ear training</li>
<li>Why and how to implement arpeggios and scales over these sequences</li>
<li>How to develop your soloing vocabulary over these sequences</li>
<li>Bass line creation over common sequences</li>
<li>And loads more...</li>
</ul>
<p>As always, see you in the shed...</p>
<p>Scott   :)</p>
